operations of consumer digital and physician outreach programs to build the institute’s brand visibility and clinical volume“it is an honor to join the danafarber family and work alongside some of the most accomplished physicians researchers and administrators anywhere” feinberg said “danafarber is a stellar organization and i’m eager to help bring its message of quality care and research to an everwider range of people”“i have known david and his work for years and am thrilled that he will be joining us” said steven singer senior vice president for communications at danafarber “david’s creativity energy and depth of experience will be a great asset to the entire danafarber community”before joining new york presbyterian feinberg led the health care practice of the seiden group an advertising and marketing firm based in new york city he began his career in the pharmaceutical and consumer industries working at procter  gamble clairol and cibageigy now novartis feinberg graduated from the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania with a bachelor of science degree in economics and from northwestern university’s kellogg school of management with a master’s degree in management and marketing   am   email   print   share media contacts for all inquiries call  and ask to speak to a member of the media team please direct emails to mediadfciharvardedu make an appointment for adults dfci quick accessappointments as soon as the next day for new adult patients for children pedionc the sixties from memory to history by david farber    hardcover  barnes  noble® up to  off with code savemore    off the criterion collection   favorite paperbacks buy  get the rd free   explore the trend shop   membership gift cards stores  events help bnlogo auto suggestions are available once you type at least  letters use up and down arrow to review and enter to select allbooksnook booksnooktextbooksbargain booksnewsstandteenskidstoys  gameshobbies  collectibleshome  giftsmovies  tvmusic ite