erlin bruxelles frankfurtm oxford wien  vi  pp  book condition new the conservative sixties tells «the other story» of america in the era of leftwing protests countercultural experiments and a civil rights revolution ten original historical essays focus on phyllis schlafly ronald reagan barry goldwater the john birch society the minutemen «moral mothers and goldwater girls» «cowboy conservatives» «national politics versus community interest» «belowthebelt politics» and the «politics of law and order» the conservative sixties demonstrates that throughout the s rightwing activists organized at the grassroots rethought their priorities discovered new allies and prepared to defeat liberals in the political and cultural arenas this history of the s puts the presidencies of ronald reagan george h bush and george w bush  as well as the conservative turn of congress and the american people  into historical perspective bookseller inventory   more information about this seller  ask bookseller a question  stock image the conservative sixties published by lang peter  isbn   isbn   new softcover first edition quantity available  from europeanmediaservice mannheim mannheim germany bookseller rating price us  convert currency shipping us  from germany to usa destination rates  speeds item description lang peter  book condition new bookseller inventory  gh more information about this seller  ask bookseller a question  stock image the conservative sixties david farber jeff roche published by peter lang inc international academic publishers  isbn   isbn   new paperback quantity available  from irish booksellers rumford me usa bookseller rating price us  convert currency shipping free within usa destination rates  speeds item description peter lang inc international academic publishers  paperback book condition new book bookseller inventory   more information about this seller  ask bookseller a question  stock image the conservative sixties david farber jeff roche published by peter l